<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-15T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-15T07:00:00-05:00" n="127" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/2127</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-15T21:00:00+09:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1918, 9 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>It is true that Baron Sakatani is going to China on March 19 to study
                                financial conditions. He called upon me to explain the object of his
                                visit, expressed fear that China faced bankruptcy, feared Chinese
                                officials would not cooperate heartily, had no definite plan to
                                suggest, and would give me benefit of his conclusions on his
                                return.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>